# azure\_monitor\_log\_profiles

Use the `azure_monitor_log_profiles` InSpec audit resource to verify a Log Profile exists.

<br />

## Syntax

An `azure_monitor_log_profiles` resource block identifies a Log Profile by name.

    describe azure_monitor_log_profiles do
      ...
    end
<br />

## Examples

### Test an example resource has a Log Profile

    describe azure_monitor_log_profiles do
      its('names') { should include('example-profile') }
    end

<br />

## Properties

* `names`

### names

The name of the Log Profile

    its('names') { should include('example-profile') }

## Matchers

This InSpec audit resource has the following special matchers. For a full list
of available matchers, please visit our [Universal Matchers page](https://www.inspec.io/docs/reference/matchers/).

### exists

The control will pass if the resource returns a result. Use `should_not` if you expect zero matches.

    # example should exist
    describe azure_monitor_log_profiles do
      its('names') { should include('example-profile') }
    end

    # texample shouldnot exist
    describe azure_monitor_log_profiles do
      its('names') { should_not include('example-profile') }
    end

## Azure Permissions

Your [Service Principal](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-resource-manager/resource-group-create-service-principal-portal) must be setup with a `contributor` role on the subscription you wish to test.